description.narrative: In 2021, Haiti continued to face humanitarian crises due to the deterioration of the socio-political and security situations and the violent 7.2 magnitude earthquake of 14 August and their incidence in terms displacement of population, disruption of services and increase of WASH needs for the most vulnerable. UNICEF supported DINEPA, the Civil Protection, donors and implementing partners to provide a well-coordinated emergency response to the earthquake and urban violence crisis and to improve the capacities of populations to face emergencies. The cholera incidence rate was kept at 0, confirming the potential elimination of cholera in Haiti.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
